User & Group Configuration

To display your UID, GID, and other permissions info
    - Run: id

To display the UID, GID, and permissions info for each user on the system.
    - Run: id <username>

To display what groups a user is in:
    - Run: groups <username>

To remove a user from a group:
    - Run `sudo usermod -G (user name) (user name).

To remove any users from the system:
    - Run: sudo deluser --remove-home (user name)

To add a group
    - Run: sudo addgroup (group name)

To remove a group:
    - Run: sudo delgroup (group name)